and I think we found our first post.

236
00:22:48,798 --> 00:22:52,427
It appeared just before the site went
up, then it was spammed Web-wide.

237
00:22:52,601 --> 00:22:55,161
"A cat caught in a rattrap.
How's that for irony?

238
00:22:55,337 --> 00:22:58,397
It's streaming live on killwithme. Com.
It's awesome. Check it out."

239
00:22:58,574 --> 00:23:01,407
It was posted by a sophomore
named Andrew Kilburn.

240
00:23:01,577 --> 00:23:05,604
It came from his account, but it didn't
actually originate from his computer.

241
00:23:05,781 --> 00:23:08,716
So our guy hacked his account
and used it to start the thread.

242
00:23:08,884 --> 00:23:11,079
- Yeah.
- Let's go after the originating IP.

243
00:23:14,990 --> 00:23:17,015
Oh, God.

244
00:23:17,193 --> 00:23:19,058
It's too bad this guy wasn't
a Boy Scout.

245
00:23:19,228 --> 00:23:21,753
He could just blink Morse code
and tell us where he is.

246
00:23:35,611 --> 00:23:39,775
Okay, I've got the "who is."
It comes back Blue Sky ISP.

247
00:23:39,949 --> 00:23:43,942
- Username and password, please.
- Coming to you now.

248
00:23:47,022 --> 00:23:49,718
- "Chang's Restaurant"?
- He hacked into their site?

249
00:23:49,892 --> 00:23:52,690
No. No. Half the office eats there.

250
00:23:52,862 --> 00:23:55,831
He's messing with us.
He wanted us to find this.

251
00:23:55,998 --> 00:23:58,125
Who the hell is this guy?

252
00:24:05,107 --> 00:24:07,598
Jennifer Marsh, Detective Eric Box.

253
00:24:07,776 --> 00:24:09,971
Portland Police has him
on the Miller abduction.

254
00:24:10,146 --> 00:24:13,513
- Jennifer's our case agent on this.
- Case agent, sir?

255
00:24:13,682 --> 00:24:15,547
- You caught it, you got it.
- Please.

256
00:24:15,718 --> 00:24:18,653
Sir, anyone else. You know I'm
on nights because of my daughter.

257
00:24:18,821 --> 00:24:20,755
I understand that, but you're it.

258
00:24:22,057 --> 00:24:23,888
- We forming a task force?
- Not yet.

259
00:24:24,059 --> 00:24:25,890
Not yet?
How much more do you need?

260
00:24:26,061 --> 00:24:29,724
So far we have one dead cat and a man
who may or may not be in danger...

261
00:24:29,899 --> 00:24:33,198
That's today. You think this is it?
It's just the beginning.

262
00:24:33,769 --> 00:24:35,259
Marsh, hold it.

263
00:24:35,437 --> 00:24:38,167
You share what you've got,
and then you take it from there.

264
00:24:38,340 --> 00:24:41,002
Appreciate your coming in, detective.

265
00:24:44,013 --> 00:24:46,277
All right. You first.

266
00:24:46,682 --> 00:24:49,583
Well, we found Miller's car
in the Rose Garden parking lot.

267
00:24:49,752 --> 00:24:51,686
No prints but his own.

268
00:24:51,854 --> 00:24:54,755
We passed out photos of the
basement to some local contractors.

269
00:24:54,924 --> 00:24:58,416
They say, judging from the timbers,
the house was built in the '20s or '30s.

270
00:24:58,594 --> 00:25:01,757
Which narrows it down to,
you know, half the city.

271
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:05,924
Yeah, what else?

272
00:25:06,101 --> 00:25:08,831
Miller appears to be a decent guy.
He's a Vietnam vet...

273
00:25:09,004 --> 00:25:11,996
...coaches his daughter's soccer,
they go to church every Sunday.

274
00:25:12,174 --> 00:25:14,301
So why'd the subject pick him?

275
00:25:15,177 --> 00:25:16,769
"Subject"?

276
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:19,113
Are we in science class?

277
00:25:19,882 --> 00:25:22,578
- What would you prefer?
- How about "piece of shit"?

278
00:25:24,186 --> 00:25:25,676
Why Miller?

279
00:25:26,322 --> 00:25:28,586
I don't know. Maybe it was random.

280
00:25:28,757 --> 00:25:30,588
What about the kitten?
Talk to that guy?

281
00:25:30,759 --> 00:25:32,989
Scotty Hillman, yeah.
He's a fucking jackass.

282
00:25:33,162 --> 00:25:35,562
All he cares about is getting
the kitten's collar...

283
00:25:35,731 --> 00:25:38,666
...because he paid 12 bucks
for it on bidityours. Com

284
00:25:38,834 --> 00:25:41,667
Which I suppose is a lot of money
if you're flipping burgers.

285
00:25:41,837 --> 00:25:45,295
What I would like to know is,
why him? Why his kitten?

286
00:25:45,474 --> 00:25:48,841
Why take the risk of stealing when
you can get one free at any shelter?

287
00:25:49,345 --> 00:25:52,075
- What do you guys got?
- It's a website.

288
00:25:52,248 --> 00:25:55,342
It's like nothing we've ever seen.
It's extremely sophisticated.

289
00:25:55,517 --> 00:25:58,611
As long as its source-streaming site
is a ghost, it's untraceable.

290
00:25:59,555 --> 00:26:02,615
This guy can invite the world to help
him kill Miller or anybody...

291
00:26:02,791 --> 00:26:05,624
...and there's not a goddamn thing
we can do about it.

292
00:26:10,266 --> 00:26:11,858
Excuse me.

293
00:26:21,277 --> 00:26:24,610
- It's over.
- Yeah.

294
00:26:25,180 --> 00:26:29,014
The numbers, they just... exploded.

295
00:26:35,357 --> 00:26:38,053
"Rolling on the floor laughing.

296
00:26:38,227 --> 00:26:39,387
Thank you for..."

297
00:26:40,262 --> 00:26:42,696
"For all your support.

298
00:26:42,865 --> 00:26:44,127
More to come."

299
00:26:46,368 --> 00:26:48,529
Well, we'll see about that.

300
00:26:52,508 --> 00:26:54,738
It's a jungle in there.

301
00:27:23,906 --> 00:27:28,138
Hey, I just went to the site
after the guy was dead...

302
00:27:28,310 --> 00:27:31,768
I got a list of assholes my girlfriends
and me think he ought to kill next.

303
00:27:31,947 --> 00:27:38,079
Last seen five days ago, FBI agents
have been working around the clock...

304
00:27:47,830 --> 00:27:49,491
There's a pickup truck.

305
00:27:49,665 --> 00:27:51,633
What's that on the back, a gun rack?

306
00:27:51,967 --> 00:27:55,801
Yeah, well, there's no way that freak is
stepping foot in my dad's country club.

307
00:27:55,971 --> 00:27:57,802
So call Tucker.

308
00:28:12,054 --> 00:28:14,887
- At 7: 15 a.m., a vehicle at the home...

309
00:28:15,057 --> 00:28:17,787
... of Oregon congressman
Joseph A. Restom.

310
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:20,929
Herbert Miller had been the focus
of an intense local...

311
00:28:21,096 --> 00:28:23,087
... and statewide police
and FBI search...

312
00:28:23,265 --> 00:28:25,631
... since midday Saturday
when he showed up...

313
00:28:25,801 --> 00:28:29,567
...on an Internet website
being tortured and murdered live.

314
00:28:29,738 --> 00:28:33,401
Now, because of the uniqueness
of the crime, and because the FBI...

315
00:28:33,575 --> 00:28:37,409
...is able to provide resources
critical to this investigation...

316
00:28:38,046 --> 00:28:42,176
...they will be leading the interagency
task force assigned to the case.

317
00:28:43,152 --> 00:28:47,282
He flew helicopters for a living. What's
his connection to a U.S. Congressman?

318
00:28:47,456 --> 00:28:51,187
Our guy had to dump the body.
Why not on a national stage?

319
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:54,659
You think he did it to get a press
conference? Build up his fan base?

320
00:28:54,830 --> 00:28:56,821
Don't call them fans.
They're accomplices.

321
00:28:56,999 --> 00:28:59,900
All right, whatever.
Why'd he choose Restom?

322
00:29:00,068 --> 00:29:01,399
He's owned by Silicon Valley.

323
00:29:01,570 --> 00:29:04,505
He sits on the House Judiciary
Committee on Net neutrality.

324
00:29:04,673 --> 00:29:07,506
No restriction on content,
all traffic treated equally.

325
00:29:07,676 --> 00:29:10,474
- Wouldn't our guy be for that?
- You'd think so.

326
00:29:10,646 --> 00:29:12,614
Miller's clients
were corporate executives.

327
00:29:12,781 --> 00:29:14,248
Maybe some were from high-tech.

328
00:29:14,416 --> 00:29:16,407
I'll track down a customer list.

329
00:29:16,585 --> 00:29:19,520
- What about the neighbors?
- One saw a van drive by at 4 a.m.

330
00:29:19,688 --> 00:29:21,781
Another heard a car door slam
a minute later.

331
00:29:21,957 --> 00:29:23,948
Figured it was the paper
being delivered.

332
00:29:24,126 --> 00:29:26,253
Excuse me a second.
Might have something here.

333
00:29:26,428 --> 00:29:28,828
- What is it?
- Tip just came in through a hot line.

334
00:29:28,997 --> 00:29:33,400
Guy named Arthur James Elmer, an
engineer at Chadwick Technologies.

335
00:29:33,569 --> 00:29:35,696
He was fired six months ago...

336
00:29:35,871 --> 00:29:38,339
...for installing a wireless Webcam
in the men's room.

337
00:29:38,507 --> 00:29:41,840
Nice. Anyway, he's been talking
about killwithme.com nonstop...

338
00:29:42,010 --> 00:29:44,274
...ever since the kitty died.
Wanna ride with us?

339
00:29:44,446 --> 00:29:46,346
Let me check this guy out
on my end.

340
00:29:46,515 --> 00:29:48,642
- We'll catch up later.
- Yeah.

341
00:30:17,446 --> 00:30:20,779
- So, what's going on?
- He won't let us in. Kind of shy.

342
00:30:28,323 --> 00:30:29,881
Elmer.

343
00:30:32,394 --> 00:30:35,886
Look, if you didn't do anything,
you got nothing to lose letting us in.

344
00:30:36,865 --> 00:30:40,357
And if you did, we can always
come back with a warrant.

345
00:30:43,171 --> 00:30:45,298
So how do you wanna play it?

346
00:30:53,582 --> 00:30:55,106
Hi.

347
00:30:56,084 --> 00:30:57,676
I'm Detective Box.

348
00:30:57,853 --> 00:31:00,083
Unusual name.

349
00:31:01,456 --> 00:31:03,617
Well, it wasn't up to me.

350
00:31:05,928 --> 00:31:09,523
So you really think I killed that guy?

351
00:31:11,133 --> 00:31:13,033
I don't know. Did you?

352
00:31:14,036 --> 00:31:15,367
Well, I'm flattered.

353
00:31:15,537 --> 00:31:18,700
I found it highly entertaining,
especially at the end.

354
00:31:18,874 --> 00:31:20,933
The way viewership
increased exponentially...

355
00:31:21,109 --> 00:31:24,272
...like some sort of epidemic.

356
00:31:25,280 --> 00:31:27,111
Can I see the basement?

357
00:32:09,524 --> 00:32:11,287
You like movies, huh?

358
00:32:12,227 --> 00:32:13,717
Yeah, who doesn't?

359
00:32:15,030 --> 00:32:16,497
Me.

360
00:32:19,034 --> 00:32:20,797
Burn your own copies?

361
00:32:20,969 --> 00:32:22,493
You know that's illegal, right?

362
00:32:33,849 --> 00:32:36,079
Can't say they didn't warn you.

363
00:32:51,333 --> 00:32:53,927
Got our proof it wasn't Elmer.

364
00:32:54,736 --> 00:32:56,431
Starting Friday at 1 p. M...

365
00:32:56,772 --> 00:33:00,799
...Elmer was logged into a chat
room for 12 consecutive hours.

366
00:33:00,976 --> 00:33:04,844
At the time Miller disappeared,
Elmer was in a steamy private chat...

367
00:33:05,013 --> 00:33:08,813
...with the first tenor of the
Men's Chorus of Greater Tacoma.

368
00:33:08,984 --> 00:33:11,111
It still felt good arresting him.

369
00:33:33,709 --> 00:33:35,609
- Hello?
- I caught you.

370
00:33:36,278 --> 00:33:40,180
- Barely. I've got a big date tonight.
- Big, special or big, large?

371
00:33:40,348 --> 00:33:44,341
I don't know. I haven't met Peggy
the secretary yet. What's up?

372
00:33:44,519 --> 00:33:48,353
I had a thought. Remember that
Andrew Kilburn guy and his review?

373
00:33:48,523 --> 00:33:50,286
Yeah, sure. What about it?

374
00:33:50,559 --> 00:33:53,084
Well, why use his account?

375
00:33:53,261 --> 00:33:56,992
I mean, maybe it wasn't random.
Maybe they know each other.

376
00:33:57,466 --> 00:33:59,696
- Yeah, it's possible.
- Yeah.

377
00:33:59,868 --> 00:34:02,996
- All right. I'll see you Sunday.
- Wait, Sunday?

378
00:34:04,372 --> 00:34:05,498
Annie's birthday.

379
00:34:06,174 --> 00:34:09,200
Oh, shit, I forgot.

380
00:34:09,377 --> 00:34:11,743
- Okay, can I bring a date?
- Are you kidding?

381
00:34:12,013 --> 00:34:14,038
You don't even know
if you like this girl.

382
00:34:14,216 --> 00:34:17,674
No, not Peggy. Melanie.
She's a social worker.

383
00:34:17,853 --> 00:34:20,413
She likes sushi and rock-climbing
and Dickens.

384
00:34:20,589 --> 00:34:24,218
- I can't believe you.
- It's a numbers game.

385
00:34:24,392 --> 00:34:27,020
Fine, fine. I gotta go.

386
00:34:27,195 --> 00:34:29,595
Okay. Hey, you got a date?

387
00:34:29,765 --> 00:34:33,758
- Good night.
- Okay. Bye. Good night, Sam.

388
00:34:47,816 --> 00:34:49,681
Molly gave me
a birthday present already.

389
00:34:49,851 --> 00:34:51,751
It's a computer game
that I downloaded.

390
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:54,946
- It's about horses.
- How sweet of her. That looks like fun.

391
00:34:55,957 --> 00:34:57,948
Not really. It's kind of silly.

392
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:03,294
- I'll show it to you later.
- Okay, honey. I love you. Gotta run.

393
00:35:34,563 --> 00:35:37,532
Come on, Annie. Let me get one first.

394
00:35:39,734 --> 00:35:41,429
Somebody order a bunch of pizzas?

395
00:35:41,603 --> 00:35:42,968
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

396
00:35:43,138 --> 00:35:45,197
- Hey, Griffin.
- For the birthday girl. Hello.

397
00:35:45,373 --> 00:35:48,206
- How are you? Over here?
- Over here.

398
00:35:50,946 --> 00:35:54,177
Listen, I only made it through
a few months of Kilburn's posts.

399
00:35:54,349 --> 00:35:56,146
- We'll need more bodies on this.
- Okay.

400
00:35:56,318 --> 00:36:01,085
He blogged, he uploaded vids, he
built sites. He practically lived online.

401
00:36:01,256 --> 00:36:04,248
- What, not anymore?
- Not since he died...

402
00:36:04,426 --> 00:36:07,793
...of something called
diabetic ketoacidosis.

403
00:36:07,963 --> 00:36:11,296
Which is what happens when you
don't take your insulin for a few days.

404
00:36:11,466 --> 00:36:14,367
Anyway, an hour after his body
was found...

405
00:36:14,536 --> 00:36:15,696
...Kill With Me went up.

406
00:36:15,871 --> 00:36:18,840
And an hour after that, Kilburn's
review was spammed Web-wide.

407
00:36:19,007 --> 00:36:22,875
- And you think our guy killed him?
- The ME called it a suicide.

408
00:36:48,270 --> 00:36:49,498
Hi.

409
00:36:49,671 --> 00:36:51,332
You're right on time.

410
00:36:51,506 --> 00:36:55,101
Yeah, well, it's a curse.
I spend half my life waiting for people.

411
00:36:55,277 --> 00:36:58,405
So... Dave Williams.

412
00:37:01,182 --> 00:37:05,619
That's a great address, by the way.
Eights bring prosperity.

413
00:37:05,787 --> 00:37:08,688
- I didn't know that.
- Yeah.

414
00:37:09,524 --> 00:37:11,617
- Come in.
- Thanks.

415
00:37:27,542 --> 00:37:28,566
Here you go, honey.

416
00:37:28,743 --> 00:37:30,802
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

417
00:37:35,550 --> 00:37:36,676
Detective.

418
00:37:36,851 --> 00:37:38,978
- Hi.
- Hi.

419
00:37:39,154 --> 00:37:42,487
Griffin invited me
to his birthday party.

420
00:37:44,059 --> 00:37:46,220
Yeah. Kind of a young crowd.

421
00:37:46,394 --> 00:37:48,453
Kind of a young crowd, Griffin.

422
00:37:48,630 --> 00:37:51,463
- Well, do you skate?
- No.

423
00:37:51,633 --> 00:37:53,658
- Thank you.
- Yeah, go ahead.

424
00:37:53,835 --> 00:37:56,668
Look, I'm gonna get out of here.
I'm sorry.

425
00:37:56,838 --> 00:38:00,672
You just got here. Don't go.
Have some pizza.

426
00:38:00,842 --> 00:38:03,811
Come on. It's not that bad.

427
00:38:13,488 --> 00:38:16,651
