428
00:38:18,660 --> 00:38:20,491
Just Korea.

429
00:38:22,864 --> 00:38:24,593
Korea.

430
00:38:25,066 --> 00:38:27,057
Well, it's fabulous.

431
00:38:28,269 --> 00:38:29,827
Thank you.

432
00:38:32,640 --> 00:38:34,574
So you gonna let me see them?

433
00:38:35,143 --> 00:38:36,838
Of course.

434
00:38:37,779 --> 00:38:39,246
Through the kitchen.

435
00:38:42,417 --> 00:38:46,649
I gotta tell you, a 710 Pullman
and a 712 Observation Car?

436
00:38:46,821 --> 00:38:48,948
My heart skipped a beat
when I got your e-mail.

437
00:38:49,124 --> 00:38:53,288
- Lf they're really in mint condition...
- My dad and I hardly ever used them.

438
00:38:53,828 --> 00:38:58,026
We mostly played foosball
and we built things.

439
00:38:59,467 --> 00:39:02,436
Toys, contraptions.

440
00:39:03,004 --> 00:39:05,029
We had a workshop.

441
00:39:05,707 --> 00:39:07,641
He died last year.

442
00:39:10,378 --> 00:39:13,404
Well, I'm sorry.

443
00:39:27,462 --> 00:39:28,063
Annie, would you come over here
for a second? Bring your skates.

444
00:39:28,063 --> 00:39:30,691
Annie, would you come over here
for a second? Bring your skates.

445
00:39:30,865 --> 00:39:33,959
- Okay.
- I want you to meet someone.

446
00:39:36,404 --> 00:39:39,464
This is Annie, the birthday girl.
This is my friend, Eric.

447
00:39:39,641 --> 00:39:41,438
- Hello, Annie.
- Hi.

448
00:39:41,609 --> 00:39:43,440
- Happy birthday.
- Thanks.

449
00:39:43,912 --> 00:39:45,812
You must be, what, 8?

450
00:39:46,314 --> 00:39:48,805
How did you know?
Everyone else thinks I'm older.

451
00:39:50,118 --> 00:39:51,585
Well, I'm a detective.

452
00:39:53,521 --> 00:39:55,921
- Are you ready to go skating finally?
- I think.

453
00:40:12,540 --> 00:40:14,565
I sure hope you like it.

454
00:40:14,742 --> 00:40:16,369
It's a punching bag.

455
00:40:16,544 --> 00:40:17,772
Okay, so you blow it up...

456
00:40:17,946 --> 00:40:20,176
...and whenever you
get in a really bad mood...

457
00:40:20,348 --> 00:40:21,906
...you sock it in the head.

458
00:40:23,251 --> 00:40:24,275
Can I do karate on it?

459
00:40:24,452 --> 00:40:28,616
Of course you can. You can do karate,
kung fu, tae kwon do.

460
00:40:28,790 --> 00:40:31,816
- Thank you, Griffin.
- You're welcome, sweetie.

461
00:40:31,993 --> 00:40:33,324
That might be my date.

462
00:40:35,530 --> 00:40:37,088
Mom.

463
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:41,225
Oh, come on.

464
00:40:41,836 --> 00:40:43,064
Happy birthday, sweetie.

465
00:40:43,238 --> 00:40:44,398
- Have fun.
- Thanks.

466
00:40:46,441 --> 00:40:48,341
Sweetheart...

467
00:40:48,843 --> 00:40:49,832
...I gotta go.

468
00:40:50,044 --> 00:40:52,877
It's a real emergency, or I
would never leave you like this.

469
00:40:53,047 --> 00:40:56,016
- I'll make it up to you, I promise. Okay?
- Okay.

470
00:40:58,720 --> 00:41:00,745
I'm looking for Griffin Dowd. He's...

471
00:41:00,922 --> 00:41:01,911
- Yeah. Hi.
- Hi.

472
00:41:02,090 --> 00:41:03,887
- I'm Melanie.
- Oh, yes. Hi, Melanie.

