01:09:53,386 --> 01:09:56,719
The thief apparently knew
his way around.

717
01:10:00,093 --> 01:10:04,553
Looks like... Looks like Griffin
was baited with a phone call.

718
01:10:04,731 --> 01:10:08,599
But we can't trace it because
it was made with a spoof card.

719
01:10:08,768 --> 01:10:11,566
Yeah, it's a phone card.
Costs about 10 bucks an hour.

720
01:10:11,738 --> 01:10:14,730
Lets you program any
caller ID you want.

721
01:10:15,975 --> 01:10:19,809
This guy breached my laptop.
He must've owned Griffin's too.

722
01:10:19,979 --> 01:10:22,470
Figured out where he was vulnerable.

723
01:10:27,887 --> 01:10:29,616
Sorry.

724
01:10:32,959 --> 01:10:35,689
I'm good at a lot of things, you know?

725
01:10:36,663 --> 01:10:39,131
But I'm not good at losing people.

726
01:10:39,299 --> 01:10:42,234
I'm bad at losing people.

727
01:11:54,040 --> 01:11:55,769
Rush-hour suicide.

728
01:11:56,976 --> 01:12:01,538
I'm pretty sure that's what Griffin was
trying to say. I'm just not sure why.

729
01:12:04,751 --> 01:12:06,480
Yeah, I remember.

730
01:12:06,652 --> 01:12:09,678
He was a professor, that guy.

731
01:12:10,156 --> 01:12:13,614
Andrew Kilburn included this
in his greatest hits.

732
01:12:15,695 --> 01:12:19,756
- I was just there, like a week ago.
- Where?

733
01:12:19,999 --> 01:12:24,197
At the Bridge Diner. You know, the
one under the Broadway Bridge.

734
01:12:24,837 --> 01:12:27,499
I was talking to Scotty Hillman...

735
01:12:27,673 --> 01:12:30,073
...the guy who owned the cat.
That's where he works.

736
01:12:31,744 --> 01:12:34,110
What was this guy's name?
Do you remember?

737
01:12:35,581 --> 01:12:39,176
No. I think
he taught Chemistry, though.

738
01:12:42,088 --> 01:12:44,648
At Marshall Junior College?

739
01:12:52,298 --> 01:12:56,496
Andrew Kilburn, a sophomore at
Portland State. Died last month...

740
01:12:56,669 --> 01:13:00,230
...but that didn't stop him
from recommending, after he died...

741
01:13:00,406 --> 01:13:03,807
...a new website called
killwithme. Com.

742
01:13:04,143 --> 01:13:08,204
How'd he do that? He didn't.
The killer did, using his account.

743
01:13:08,381 --> 01:13:11,145
When Agent Griffin Dowd's
investigation revealed why...

744
01:13:11,317 --> 01:13:13,410
...this deceased college student
was chosen...

745
01:13:13,586 --> 01:13:17,750
...to promote the Kill With Me site,
it cost him his life.

746
01:13:22,028 --> 01:13:24,292
This is James Reilly.

747
01:13:24,664 --> 01:13:25,892
Sixteen months ago...

748
01:13:26,065 --> 01:13:29,091
...depressed over the recent death
of his wife, a hematologist...

749
01:13:29,268 --> 01:13:33,500
...Reilly staggered out into rush-hour
traffic on the Broadway Bridge.

750
01:13:33,673 --> 01:13:35,573
Traffic copters were out in force...

751
01:13:35,741 --> 01:13:38,608
...but only one caught all the action
from beginning to end...

752
01:13:38,778 --> 01:13:40,211
...Channel 12.

753
01:13:40,880 --> 01:13:44,509
The regular pilot was out sick that day,
so the job went to Herbert Miller.

754
01:13:45,985 --> 01:13:50,888
He later told friends he'd gotten lucky.
At the right place at the right time.

755
01:13:55,695 --> 01:13:57,185
The back of Reilly's skull...

756
01:13:57,363 --> 01:14:00,890
...landed on the rooftop
of this diner. So did his glasses.

757
01:14:01,067 --> 01:14:03,035
The skull was turned over
to the coroner...

758
01:14:03,202 --> 01:14:06,694
...but the glasses were retrieved
by one of the diner's employees...

759
01:14:06,873 --> 01:14:08,067
...Scotty Hillman.

760
01:14:08,908 --> 01:14:10,808
He put them up for sale online.

761
01:14:10,977 --> 01:14:12,740
And they sold quickly.

762
01:14:12,912 --> 01:14:15,176
Kids were home from school.
Parents were outraged.

763
01:14:15,348 --> 01:14:17,908
They called the TV stations.
The TV stations apologized.

764
01:14:18,084 --> 01:14:19,483
Except for Channel 12.

765
01:14:19,652 --> 01:14:23,110
They'd been having a little problem
in the ratings, but not that afternoon.

766
01:14:23,289 --> 01:14:24,916
Their numbers were sky-high.

767
01:14:25,091 --> 01:14:27,616
And knowing a good thing
when it fell into their lap...

768
01:14:27,793 --> 01:14:30,091
...they rushed a veteran reporter
to the scene.

769
01:14:30,263 --> 01:14:31,457
This is David Williams...

770
01:14:31,631 --> 01:14:34,464
He got lucky, landed an interview
with a local businessman...

771
01:14:34,634 --> 01:14:37,694
...whose parked Cadillac had been
struck by Reilly's falling body.

772
01:14:37,870 --> 01:14:39,132
When the interview ended...

773
01:14:39,305 --> 01:14:42,297
...Channel 12, as a courtesy to
those who might have missed it...

774
01:14:42,475 --> 01:14:44,841
...aired the entire video one last time.

775
01:14:45,011 --> 01:14:47,775
Within minutes, Andrew Kilburn
had pulled it off his TiVo...

776
01:14:47,947 --> 01:14:51,075
...and posted it on five different
shock-video sites.

777
01:14:51,250 --> 01:14:54,378
From there, Reilly's suicide
was public domain.

778
01:14:54,554 --> 01:14:59,685
Something for five billion people
to feed on, laugh at, gossip about.

779
01:14:59,859 --> 01:15:01,793
Reilly had a son, Owen.

780
01:15:02,929 --> 01:15:06,296
He was brilliant. Good at electronics,
mechanics and computers...

781
01:15:06,465 --> 01:15:09,798
... but he was disturbed.
He was troubled. He was withdrawn.

782
01:15:10,436 --> 01:15:12,768
Owen took his father's suicide
very hard.

783
01:15:12,939 --> 01:15:16,705
He had to be hospitalized.
And six months ago he was released.

784
01:15:17,476 --> 01:15:20,343
This x-ray image is supposed to be
Owen's father.

785
01:15:20,513 --> 01:15:23,209
The number on the left,
the date his father died...

786
01:15:24,217 --> 01:15:27,482
...followed by the number
of his autopsy report.

787
01:15:27,887 --> 01:15:30,788
Owen lives alone now
at his father's house in Fairview.

788
01:15:30,957 --> 01:15:33,221
What do you say we arrest
the piece of shit?

789
01:15:35,056 --> 01:15:36,717
Go! Go!

790
01:16:12,327 --> 01:16:13,589
Basement's clear!

791
01:16:28,643 --> 01:16:30,440
This is bad.

792
01:17:04,012 --> 01:17:07,072
There are new developments
in the Internet murder investigation...

793
01:17:07,248 --> 01:17:10,740
... tonight out of Portland, Oregon.
For more, let's turn to Marilyn Deutsch.

794
01:17:10,918 --> 01:17:13,648
Right. Police now say they know
who is kidnapping people...

795
01:17:13,821 --> 01:17:16,756
... in this area and then killing them
live on the Web.

796
01:17:17,125 --> 01:17:20,891
Take a look at this picture. Police say
the suspect's name is Owen Reilly.

797
01:17:21,062 --> 01:17:24,828
He is 20 years old,
and just nine months ago...

798
01:17:25,566 --> 01:17:27,158
First...

799
01:17:27,335 --> 01:17:30,862
...I just wanted to say how sorry I am.

800
01:17:31,439 --> 01:17:34,237
This was a loss for all of us...

801
01:17:34,409 --> 01:17:37,606
...but most deeply for you,
and we know that. I know that.

802
01:17:39,714 --> 01:17:44,276
You've done everything you
possibly could. You've given enough.

803
01:17:45,486 --> 01:17:49,115
- I want you to take some time off.
- What?

804
01:17:49,624 --> 01:17:52,718
Why? Because now it's personal?

805
01:17:52,894 --> 01:17:55,158
This guy's still running around,
the case is open.

806
01:17:55,329 --> 01:17:56,694
The kid's face is everywhere.

807
01:17:56,864 --> 01:18:00,231
He's driving around in a 40-year-old
VW bus with electronics in it.

808
01:18:00,401 --> 01:18:02,062
We'll have him
by this time tomorrow.

809
01:18:02,236 --> 01:18:05,603
- Maybe.
- Jennifer, I'm not only thinking of you.

810
01:18:07,041 --> 01:18:10,340
Now join your family. Just for a week.

811
01:18:12,714 --> 01:18:14,841
I'll take a day.

812
01:19:05,099 --> 01:19:07,465
- Hey.
- Hey.

813
01:19:08,002 --> 01:19:11,028
So, what'd he say?

814
01:19:11,806 --> 01:19:13,899
He told me to get lost.

815
01:19:15,576 --> 01:19:16,941
Well, he's right.

816
01:19:19,814 --> 01:19:21,941
And what did you say?

817
01:19:27,889 --> 01:19:29,720
That's what I figured.

818
01:21:22,169 --> 01:21:24,831
This has been America News Radio.

819
01:21:25,006 --> 01:21:28,498
Now back to your local
ANR station for news.

820
01:21:29,143 --> 01:21:31,839
Good evening.
You're listening to KMZR, Portland.

821
01:21:32,013 --> 01:21:34,982
This is the news at the top
of the 10:00 hour.

822
01:21:35,149 --> 01:21:37,777
Dominating the news again here
and across the nation...

823
01:21:37,952 --> 01:21:40,978
... is the increasingly urgent search
for the Internet killer...

824
01:21:41,155 --> 01:21:44,249
... now known to be
Owen Reilly of Portland.

825
01:21:44,425 --> 01:21:48,521
His most recent victim, an FBI
cyber-crimes agent, Griffin Dowd...

826
01:21:48,696 --> 01:21:52,188
... was discovered dead in Reilly's
Fairview home basement this morning.

827
01:21:52,900 --> 01:21:56,233
In what the FBI is describing as
the most serious Internet crime wave...

828
01:21:56,404 --> 01:21:58,929
... since the computer age began...

829
01:22:45,219 --> 01:22:46,208
Shit!

830
01:22:48,622 --> 01:22:50,351
Hello, Jennifer.

831
01:22:55,963 --> 01:22:57,828
Look out the front window.

832
01:22:58,632 --> 01:23:00,896
Under that streetlight.

833
01:23:02,236 --> 01:23:05,364
That's where my father's body
fell over the railing.

834
01:23:05,539 --> 01:23:07,939
Some websites show the whole
thing in slow motion...

835
01:23:08,109 --> 01:23:11,340
... because it's just so much
better that way.

836
01:23:13,147 --> 01:23:16,207
One archives it in a section
called "whoa."

837
01:23:16,917 --> 01:23:20,409
That's it. Just "whoa."

838
01:23:21,722 --> 01:23:23,849
You and the people you work with...

839
01:23:24,892 --> 01:23:28,020
... you let people say and do
almost anything they want.

840
01:23:28,195 --> 01:23:30,356
It doesn't matter who it hurts.

841
01:23:33,834 --> 01:23:35,961
I'm sorry, Owen.

842
01:23:39,673 --> 01:23:41,664
Owen, are you there?

843
01:24:17,111 --> 01:24:18,738
- Call Answering Center.
- Listen.

844
01:24:18,913 --> 01:24:20,437
I'm an agent with the FBI.

845
01:24:20,614 --> 01:24:23,708
I need you to connect me
to the Portland field office.

846
01:24:23,884 --> 01:24:24,976
Do you understand?

847
01:24:37,598 --> 01:24:40,089
- Yeah.
- It's Owen!

848
01:24:40,267 --> 01:24:43,031
He's hacked into my car's
computer and my cell phone.

849
01:24:43,204 --> 01:24:44,637
I'm on the Broadway Bridge.

850
01:24:44,805 --> 01:24:47,365
Don't move. I'll send a
black-and-white. Stay there.

851
01:24:47,741 --> 01:24:49,231
All right.

852
01:25:47,535 --> 01:25:49,628
- Box.
- Lieutenant, I'm on the bridge.

853
01:25:49,803 --> 01:25:51,236
There's no sign of Marsh.

854
01:25:51,405 --> 01:25:54,272
Okay. Relay that to FBI Portland.
I'm minutes away.

855
01:25:55,142 --> 01:25:57,406
- Hurry. Get the director on the phone.
- Yes, sir.

856
01:25:57,578 --> 01:26:00,012
Shut down every road to and from
the Broadway Bridge.

857
01:26:00,181 --> 01:26:02,206
Every car gets stopped now.

858
01:27:03,877 --> 01:27:07,142
I need you to run a check
on a 2006 Saab.

859
01:27:07,314 --> 01:27:09,908
Get me a location, start tracking.
Name: Jennifer Marsh.

860
01:27:10,084 --> 01:27:11,813
Portland, Oregon.

861
01:27:53,394 --> 01:27:56,522
Fucker disabled her car's computer.
We can't track her.

862
01:28:06,140 --> 01:28:07,539
Hello.

863
01:28:49,016 --> 01:28:50,711
You know...

864
01:28:50,884 --> 01:28:55,321
...l'm only doing to you
what they're going to do to me.

865
01:28:56,523 --> 01:28:58,150
Only...

866
01:28:58,459 --> 01:29:03,624
...they'll use potassium chloride, and
they won't let very many people watch.

867
01:29:05,065 --> 01:29:07,158
But not for long.

868
01:29:10,838 --> 01:29:12,203
You see, soon...

869
01:29:13,640 --> 01:29:18,475
...executions will be delivered
live to our TVs...

870
01:29:18,912 --> 01:29:23,906
...our computers, our phones,
our handhelds...

871
01:29:24,385 --> 01:29:27,286
...and it won't cost much.

872
01:29:27,454 --> 01:29:30,480
Maybe 10 bucks.

873
01:29:39,133 --> 01:29:40,998
Millions of eyes...

874
01:29:42,669 --> 01:29:46,070
...all watching the same thing
at the same time.

875
01:29:47,040 --> 01:29:49,565
One big, happy family.

876
01:29:51,478 --> 01:29:53,639
And all of it brought to you by...

877
01:29:59,253 --> 01:30:01,187
It doesn't matter.

878
01:30:05,092 --> 01:30:07,788
They'll have no trouble
finding sponsors.

879
01:30:39,660 --> 01:30:42,128
What's going on?
We have a signal?

880
01:30:42,296 --> 01:30:43,558
We're still locked out.

881
01:30:43,730 --> 01:30:46,096
- Stay on it.
- Yes, sir.

882
01:31:08,522 --> 01:31:11,821
I wonder if they'll kill you
faster or slower.

883
01:31:14,161 --> 01:31:16,857
Based on what I've seen online...

884
01:31:17,731 --> 01:31:21,326
...the awful things that men do to
women that other men pay to watch...

885
01:31:25,639 --> 01:31:28,164
...my guess would be faster.

886
01:31:31,979 --> 01:31:33,913
Much faster.

887
01:31:53,066 --> 01:31:55,591
Jesus Christ, it's Marsh!

888
01:32:08,982 --> 01:32:12,577
- This is Box.
- It's Brooks. He's got Marsh on his site.

889
01:32:13,554 --> 01:32:15,283
Send it to me.

890
01:33:35,302 --> 01:33:37,327
You're giving me my best numbers.

891
01:33:41,241 --> 01:33:44,301
That's... That's her basement.
He's got her in her own basement.

892
01:33:59,126 --> 01:34:00,559
No, no.

893
01:34:12,773 --> 01:34:15,037
- Did you see that?
- Fuck!

894
01:34:17,744 --> 01:34:19,268
Fuck!

895
01:34:41,768 --> 01:34:43,292
Yes!

